article.headline: New Mexico St. 70, Hawaii 59
article.story: HONOLULU -- Troy Gillenwater scored 18 points and Wendell McKines added 16 points and 11 rebounds to lead New Mexico State to a 70-59 win over Hawaii on Saturday. Gillenwater also grabbed eight rebounds as the Aggies shot 49 percent from the field. New Mexico State (16-14, 9-7 WAC) also got 13 points from Jonathan Gibson and 10 from Hernst Laroche. Kareem Nitoto led Hawaii (13-16, 5-11 WAC) with 11 points. The Aggies almost exclusively used a zone defense to hold the Rainbow Warriors to 32 percent shooting from the field.
